x4freetext: CGR 560 cyclotron
External deuteron beam of
CGR 560 cyclotron of VUB, Brussels was used to
irradiate stacks at 21.1 and 15.1 MeV.
The stack contained the target foils and Ti
12.1 micron monitor foils. The irradiation was done
for half an hour at 200 nA beam current.
The beam parameters was determined by using the
monitor foils.
Samples were measured three times. Two measurements
close to EOB and one measurement 1 month after EOB to
allow decay of short lived products.
Energy degradation was calculated by using the
polinomial formula of Andersen and Ziegler, 1977.
The whole excitation functions of the monitor reactions
was remeasured and compared to the recommended values.
High purity Pt foils 12.1 and 13.4 micron thick were
used from GoodFellow.
The complete excitation
function of the used monitor reactions was remeasured
and compared with the recommended curve.
chapter 4
The uncertainty of the primary beam 0.3 MeV
and the estimated mid-energy of the target foils
reached max. 2.0 MeV at the low energy side.
Total errors were given. Correction of the beam
was made using the monitor reactions.
Contributing errors:
number of target nuclei            1%
beam intensity                     7%
detector efficiency                5%
peak area and statistical error 1-10%
nuclear data                     1-5%
The measured experimental data were compared to
and analyzed with theoretical calculations based on
the model code ALICE-IPPE.
On the basis of the new experimental cross
sections integral yields were calculated.
approved by F.Tarkanyi.
